    public interface Asset
    Interface representing a given ("crypto") asset in its most abstract form, having a name, eg "Bitcoin", a ticker symbol, eg "BTC", and an address validation function. Together, these properties represent the minimum information and functionality required to register and trade an asset on the Bisq network.

    Implementations typically extend either the Coin or Token base classes, and must be registered in the META-INF/services/bisq.asset.Asset file in order to be available in the AssetRegistry at runtime.

    Since:
    0.7.0
    Author:
    Chris Beams
